  <!-- IMPORTANT ALERT -->
  <div style="background:#1a1508;border:1px solid #7c5c10;border-radius:10px;padding:14px 18px;margin-bottom:20px;font-size:13px;color:#fbbf24">
    ⚠️ <strong>Critical note:</strong> The Macan has TWO completely different generations. <strong>2021–2023 = Gas (old gen, turbocharged 4-cyl or V6)</strong>. <strong>2024+ Macan Electric = Entirely new platform</strong> (PPE, same as Taycan), 100% electric, no gas option. The 2025 gas models listed at Mark Motors are remaining old-gen inventory still being sold as CPO. If you want gas, stick to 2021–2023 (or 2025 gas CPO stock). Budget-wise: gas Macans are your only realistic option under $70k.
