      <div>
        <div style="font-size:13px;font-weight:800;color:#f59e0b;margin-bottom:4px">Ottawa Winter Reality Check</div>
        <div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--muted);line-height:1.7">The 718 Boxster is a <strong style="color:#fff">rear-wheel-drive convertible</strong> with a low, wide stance. It is <strong style="color:#f87171">not suitable as a primary vehicle in Ottawa</strong> where you'll see 4+ months of snow, ice, and road salt. If you buy a Boxster, plan to garage it October–April and have a second car (or assume Uber costs). That said — for 5 months of pure driving bliss, it's arguably the most rewarding car on this list.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

