<!-- ============================== RECOMMENDATIONS TAB ============================== -->
<div id="tab-recommend" class="section">
  <h2 class="section-title">Who Should Buy What?</h2>
  <p class="section-sub">Personalized picks based on priorities — for your Ottawa area budget of up to $70k</p>

  <div class="rec-grid" id="rec-grid">

    <div class="rec-card" style="border-color: var(--genesis)">
      <div class="persona">🏆 Best Overall Value</div>
      <h4>Genesis GV70 Advanced Plus</h4>
      <p>If you want the most car for money — massaging seats, HUD, panoramic roof, ventilated seats, 300hp AWD — and you don't need the German badge, nothing in this list comes close at $49,490. J.D. Power #1 reliability to boot.</p>
      <div class="pick" style="color:var(--genesis)">→ 2024 GV70 Advanced Plus @ $49,490</div>
    </div>

    <div class="rec-card" style="border-color: var(--audi)">
      <div class="persona">❄️ Best for Ottawa Winters</div>
      <h4>Audi Q5 with Quattro</h4>
      <p>Quattro is universally recognized as the best AWD system for Canadian winters. The CPO listing at Audi West Ottawa ($58,888, 3.49% rate) means you get peace of mind warranty, lower rate, and the best snow car in this list.</p>
      <div class="pick" style="color:var(--audi)">→ 2022 Q5 Progressiv CPO @ $58,888 (Ottawa)</div>
    </div>

    <div class="rec-card" style="border-color: var(--lexus)">
      <div class="persona">🔧 Lowest Total Cost of Ownership</div>
      <h4>Lexus RX 350</h4>
      <p>~$900/yr maintenance (vs $1,800–2,400 for BMW/Mercedes), best resale value, Consumer Reports #1 reliability. If you plan to keep the car 5–8 years, the RX pays for itself vs German alternatives.</p>
      <div class="pick" style="color:var(--lexus)">→ 2023 RX 350 Premium AWD @ ~$58,500</div>
    </div>

    <div class="rec-card" style="border-color: var(--porsche)">
      <div class="persona">🏎️ If the Badge Matters</div>
      <h4>Porsche Macan CPO</h4>
      <p>The 2021 CPO at Gatineau ($44,995, Porsche Approved 24-month warranty) is the best-risk Porsche you can get under $60k near Ottawa. The 2022 Macan S ($66,900) gets you 375hp and more tech but stretches the budget.</p>
      <div class="pick" style="color:var(--porsche)">→ 2021 Macan CPO @ $44,995 (Gatineau)</div>
    </div>

    <div class="rec-card" style="border-color: #4d85b8">
      <div class="persona">🛡️ Safety First</div>
      <h4>Volvo XC60</h4>
      <p>IIHS Top Safety Pick+ every single year — no other car on this list matches it. If you have a family and safety is the #1 priority, the XC60 is the answer. The Recharge PHEV variant (455hp combined) is outstanding if you have a plug.</p>
      <div class="pick" style="color:#4d85b8">→ 2023 XC60 R-Design @ ~$51,000</div>
    </div>

    <div class="rec-card" style="border-color: var(--bmw)">
      <div class="persona">🏁 Best Performance / Driver's Car</div>
      <h4>BMW X5 or 530i xDrive</h4>
      <p>BMW's 3.0L I6 in the X5 (335hp) is genuinely thrilling. If you want an SUV that handles like a sport car, the X5 M Sport at $57,800 (Kitchener, 34k km) is the pick. For a sedan, the 530i xDrive has the best driving dynamics in class.</p>
      <div class="pick" style="color:var(--bmw)">→ 2022 X5 M Sport @ $57,800 (Kitchener)</div>
    </div>

    <div class="rec-card" style="border-color: var(--genesis)">
      <div class="persona">👨‍👩‍👧‍👦 Best for Families (Mid-Size)</div>
      <h4>Genesis GV80</h4>
      <p>7-seat option, quilted nappa leather, panoramic, heads-up display, and the Genesis 5-year 100k warranty — all for ~$59,900 used. Competes directly with the GLE and Q7 but at a significant price advantage.</p>
      <div class="pick" style="color:var(--genesis)">→ 2023 GV80 Advanced @ ~$59,900</div>
    </div>

    <div class="rec-card" style="border-color: var(--mercedes)">
      <div class="persona">🎭 Most Luxurious Interior</div>
      <h4>Mercedes GLC 300 or E-Class</h4>
      <p>If the interior ambiance matters most — ambient lighting, MBUX voice assistant, hyperscreen displays — Mercedes wins. The GLC is more practical; the E-Class more refined. Both stretch to or slightly above $70k for 2023+ examples.</p>
      <div class="pick" style="color:#999">→ 2023 GLC 300 4MATIC @ ~$57,500</div>
    </div>

    <div class="rec-card" style="border-color: #CD853F">
      <div class="persona">🏔️ Most Space in a Porsche</div>
      <h4>Porsche Cayenne (2022 — Best Value)</h4>
      <p>If you want a Porsche that fits a family, the Cayenne is the answer. The 2022 Prem Plus ($65,900, 51k km, Vaughan) hits the sweet spot — newest year, lowest km, fully loaded with HUD and panoramic. The V6 335hp base engine is genuinely powerful. Drive to GTA once, win forever.</p>
      <div class="pick" style="color:#CD853F">→ 2022 Cayenne Prem Plus @ $65,900 / 51k km (Vaughan)</div>
    </div>

    <div class="rec-card" style="border-color: #4472C4">
      <div class="persona">🏎️ Weekend Thrill Machine</div>
      <h4>Porsche 718 Boxster (2020 — Orléans Gem)</h4>
      <p>If you have a daily driver for winter and want something purely joyful May–October, the 2020 Boxster in Orléans (16km away!) is a unicorn — manual gearbox, only 16,500 km, private seller. A garage-kept Porsche sports car practically in your backyard. Get a pre-purchase inspection, then jump on it.</p>
      <div class="pick" style="color:#4472C4">→ 2020 718 Boxster Manual @ $69,800 / 16,500 km (Orléans, 16km)</div>
    </div>

  </div>

  <div style="background: var(--surface); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 14px; padding: 24px; margin-top: 24px;">
